U.S. SENIOR OPEN CHAMPIONSHIP
August 1, 2010
Michael Allen
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT









   MICHAEL ALLEN: I played okay but not great. A lot of holes, really -- the pins were more accessible today, and I hit some good tee shots and put the ball in play. 

 Q. The last nine holes everyone says are better today. 
 MICHAEL ALLEN: I thought they were. 
 That was my thing, I really hit the -- kept the ball in play. Each day got easier after the first day. 

 Q. You have to be happy about your round. 
 MICHAEL ALLEN: Yeah, I was hoping to be a contender here but it's been a wonderful week and the crowds turned out great and supported us, so this was great. 

 Q. What do you think of Bernhard Langer picking off the --
 MICHAEL ALLEN: A lot of guys -- he's pretty unflappable, that guy. He's pretty solid. He's not going to give it away. 

 Q. Thank you.







END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT